Yang Haodong gave a speech on the spirit of the 19th National Congress of the Communist Party of China's 6th Plenary Session and the Provincial Party Congress in Ma'anshan Mountain.
Drawing strength from the hundred-year struggle of the Party.
According to the unified arrangements of the Provincial Party Committee, on the morning of December 10, Yang Haodong, a Standing Committee member and Minister of Propaganda of the Provincial Party Committee, gave an interactive speech at the Ma'anshan Video and Cultural Park, deeply studying and implementing the spirit of the 19th National Congress of the Communist Party of China's 6th Plenary Session, studying and implementing General Secretary Xi Jinping's important speeches and instructions on Hunan, and studying and implementing the spirit of the 12th Provincial Party Congress.
Yang Haodong, from the perspectives of ideal belief and original mission, self-revolution and youthful party, party leadership and party theory, combined his own insights and personal experiences, to comprehensively and systematically explain the core essence and practical requirements of the plenary session's spirit.
He pointed out that the spirit of the plenary session, the important speeches and instructions of General Secretary Xi Jinping on Hunan, and the spirit of the Provincial Party Congress should be combined and studied, and the ideas, political consciousness, and actions of defending the "two established" and "two maintained" should be strengthened, and we should firmly move forward in the direction guided by General Secretary Xi Jinping.
During the interactive exchange session, representatives from the grass-roots cadres, enterprises, and youth raised questions about the relationship between the three historical resolutions, how to understand the decisive meaning of "two establisments", how cultural enterprises should grasp the direction, and how young people in the new era can draw strength from the hundred-year history of the party. Yang Haodong answered each question with common language and vivid examples. He earnestly exhorted young party members to draw on the strength of the hundred-year history of the party's struggles, to closely unite around the central party leadership, to firmly follow the party, and to write responsibility and dedication with youth.